ium temperature of ~970 K, at which Na can form various\ncompounds. We also briefly discuss the use of Gaussian process and wavelet\nmethods to account for time correlated noise in transit light curves.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 29 Oct 2012 20:00:00 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 24 Apr 2013 14:08:47 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-11"}
